data.meta_description: I’m Eliza! 23 (she/her) Storyboard artist on SpongeBob! 🧽 Lover of all things vintage, weird, wacky, and everything in between. Cartoon fanatic and fugitive from the funny papers.
data.text:
Animatic to final for "The Patrick Show After Dark"! Posting as a companion piece to some more boards I uploaded prior since still frames don't do it justice all the way. I cannooooooooot get over how talented our background team is--I want a coffee table book made up of backgrounds from this episode alone! I love how atmospheric and colorful it is!

a bit of a "sleeper agent" cartoon in that it may seem innocuous now, but is actually an important cartoon of many firsts and holds up remarkably well, The Squawkin' Hawk does inaugurate a handful of important milestones. the birth of Henery Hawk--who was indeed a creation of Chuck Jones', not Bob McKimson's--is one of them. this being the first collaboration between Jones and Mike Maltese is the other. Henery may sound and look a bit different than he is most known for, but his lust for chicken is clearly demonstrated from day 1 in this fast paced, clever romp that would later be retooled as You Were Never Duckier. tired of being condescended to, Henery sets out to nab a chicken of his own for dinner, but is met with predictable pushback when biting off more than he can chew.

i talk often about how i relate to Daffy (and by proxy Porky as well) more than any other fictional character and it's true. but i just need to put it out there that i have such a strong kinship with good ol SpongeBob. i have only related to him more as i've gotten older. i just had a 2 hour meeting that resulted in my coworkers likening me to SB and complimenting my enthusiasm and i'm riding on cloud 9. i love this exuberant obsessive hardworking Sponge
